# CSS Guidelines

## Architecture
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) for theming
- Implement dark mode with `[data-theme="dark"]` attribute
- Follow mobile-first responsive design approach
- Use BEM-like naming convention for classes

## Theming System
- Define color variables in `:root` for light mode
- Override variables for dark mode using `[data-theme="dark"]`
- Respect system preference with `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`
- Use consistent color palette: accent-green (#10b981) as primary

## Responsive Design
- Breakpoints: 768px (tablet), 480px (mobile)
- Use flexible units (rem, em, %) over fixed pixels
- Implement smooth transitions with `cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`
- Ensure touch-friendly interactive elements (min 44px)

## Performance
- Use efficient selectors
- Minimize CSS specificity conflicts
- Group related styles together
- Use `transform` and `opacity` for animations (GPU accelerated)

## Dark Mode Implementation
- Store theme preference in localStorage
- Provide smooth transitions between themes
- Update toggle button icon and aria-label
- Maintain consistent visual hierarchy in both modes